{"title":"Salsa Cycles’ Stormchaser Gravel Race Bike Rolls In with New Specs and Colors","link":"https://bikerumor.com/salsa-cycles-stormchaser-gravel-race-bike-new-specs-and-colors/","date":1718294400000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-hero-e1718236175208.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"537\" alt=\"(Photos/Salsa Cycles)\" /></p>\n<p>Minnesota’s <a href=\"https://www.salsacycles.com/\">Salsa Cycles</a> is known for building some iconic adventure race bikes, and the <a href=\"https://www.salsacycles.com/bikes/road/Stormchaser\" target=\"_blank\">Stormchaser gravel bike</a> is no exception. Bult for adverse conditions, the versatile Stormchaser will be now available in four different flavors. Two singlespeed options, as a frameset, or a geared version that comes with front suspension. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-berry-front-side.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-berry-front-side.jpeg\" alt=\"Salsa Cycles Stormchaser berry front side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-berry-front-side.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-berry-front-side-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-berry-front-side-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-berry-front-side-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-berry-front-side-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-berry-front-side-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Stormchaser Apex Eagle with Suspension, in the new Berry color (Photos/Salsa Cycles)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Salsa Cycles says the Stormchaser’s name comes from “<em>the bike’s perseverance on weather-wrecked gravel roads. It’s a bike designed to reach the end of the ride no matter what, and to do so without being completely ruined on the way. It’s no coincidence that many of the biggest gravel races take place in Tornado Alley.</em>“</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s touch on the different configurations that are available for the Stormchaser. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Stormchaser Single Speed</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $1799</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Color: Storm Gray</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-Storm-Gray-singlespeed.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"734\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-Storm-Gray-singlespeed.jpeg\" alt=\"Salsa Cycles Stormchaser Storm Gray singlespeed\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-Storm-Gray-singlespeed.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-Storm-Gray-singlespeed-297x170.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-Storm-Gray-singlespeed-120x69.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-Storm-Gray-singlespeed-768x440.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-singlespeed-front-side.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"1001\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-singlespeed-front-side.jpeg\" alt=\"Salsa Cycles Stormchaser singlespeed front side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-singlespeed-front-side.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-singlespeed-front-side-297x232.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-singlespeed-front-side-120x94.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-singlespeed-front-side-768x601.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-singlespeed-rear-side.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"977\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-singlespeed-rear-side.jpeg\" alt=\"Salsa Cycles Stormchaser singlespeed rear side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-singlespeed-rear-side.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-singlespeed-rear-side-297x227.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-singlespeed-rear-side-120x92.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-singlespeed-rear-side-768x586.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Highlights</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>6066-T6 aluminum frame </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Class 5™ VRS (Vibration Reduction System)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Gravel race geometry</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Carbon fiber fork</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Alternator Flat Mount dropout</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Extra mud clearance and abrasion-resistant fork plates</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Rack mounts, Three-Pack mounts, and top-tube and down-tube accessory mounts</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fender mounts</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Stealth dropper post-routing</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Includes 17t and 18t cog installed</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Stormchaser Apex Eagle Sus</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $3199</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Color: Berry</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-hero-e1718236175208.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"537\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-hero-e1718236175208.jpeg\" alt=\"Salsa Cycles Stormchaser hero\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/Salsa-Cycles-Stormchaser-hero-e1718